SUM(column_name): Calculates the total sum of a numeric column. For example:

text
SELECT SUM(Salary)
FROM Employees;
This returns the total salary across all employees.

*COUNT(column_name or ): Counts how many rows (or non-null column values) exist. For example:

text
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM Employees;
This returns the number of employees.

AVG(column_name): Computes the average value of a numeric column. For example:

text
SELECT AVG(Salary)
FROM Employees;
This returns the average salary.

